            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EThe%20bride%20spoken%20of%20in%20Revelation%2021%3A2%20provides%20us%20with%20an%20appropriate%20description%20of%20the%20city%20of%20the%20New%20Jerusalem%2C%20filled%20with%20the%20faithful%20believers%20in%20Christ.%20All%20history%20closes%20with%20a%20description%20of%20the%20marriage%20of%20Christ%20to%20His%20Church%2C%20an%20eternal%20romance%20in%20which%20believers%20will%20be%20in%20covenant%20with%20Him%20forever.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThis%20description%20of%20the%20Bride%20of%20Christ%20is%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20a%20picture%20of%20a%20godly%20marriage.%20It%20symbolizes%20a%20covenant%20of%20faithfulness%20and%20commitment%20so%20that%20all%20the%20world%20may%20see%20how%20Christ%20will%20care%20for%20His%20Church.%20For%20this%20reason%2C%20God%20declared%20his%20hatred%20of%20divorce%20(Malachi%202%3A16)%2C%20as%20it%20destroys%20the%20beautiful%20picture%20of%20covenant%20faithfulness.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EProverbs%2031%3A10-24%20describes%20%22a%20virtuous%20and%20capable%20wife.%22%20Her%20beauty%2C%20grace%2C%20wisdom%2C%20and%20faithfulness%2C%20as%20well%20as%20her%20relationship%20with%20her%20offspring%20and%20husband%2C%20all%20portray%20the%20qualities%20of%20the%20Bride%20of%20Christ.%20All%20that%20God%20is%20working%20in%20your%20life%20is%20designed%20to%20prepare%20you%20to%20be%20married%20to%20Christ%20forever.%20One%20day%2C%20the%20Holy%20Spirit%20will%20usher%20the%20Church%20to%20the%20gate%20of%20heaven%20and%20then%20march%20her%20down%20the%20main%20street%20of%20the%20New%20Jerusalem%20to%20be%20married%20to%20Christ.%20%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EGet%20ready%2C%20Bride%20of%20Christ.%20Your%20greatest%20day%20is%20approaching!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
